## Dockerfile

```dockerfile
FROM nginx:alpine

COPY . /usr/share/nginx/html

EXPOSE 80
```

## CI/CD Workflow

The GitHub Actions workflow performs the following tasks:

1. Triggers automatically on every push to the main branch.
2. Checks out the source code from the repository.
3. Logs in to Docker Hub using GitHub Secrets.
4. Builds the Docker image.
5. Pushes the image to Docker Hub.
6. Makes the latest image available for deployment.

